  "texts": [
    "Based on Fig. 2, for most LLMs the AUPRC difference increases as the dataset got more imbalanced.",
    "This can be explained by how the AUPRC is calculated.",
    "Since we define option A as positive when plotting the AUPRC, the scarcity of option A being the correct label plays an important role in determining the precision and the recall, which are the keys to the PRC curve.",
    "As the number of options A being correct gets lower, any false classification will be magnified, which enlarges the differences between the two probabilities if one is better than the other.",
    "We do not show the results under the 70% and 90% imbalance rates since they are very similar to the ones under the 50% imbalance ratio."
  ],
